Dialogue: 0,0:00:03.58,0:00:05.12,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,No otter what happens, I'm still your partner.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:05.54,0:00:06.96,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Today, we go back ten years...
Dialogue: 0,0:00:06.96,0:00:09.59,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,As we try to find the truth behind the red clues!
Dialogue: 0,0:00:09.84,0:00:11.21,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Recognizing that single truth,
Dialogue: 0,0:00:11.21,0:00:12.63,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,a child with the intellect of an adult...
Dialogue: 0,0:00:12.63,0:00:14.17,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,His name is: Detective Conan!
Dialogue: 0,0:01:41.55,0:01:45.10,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Kobayashi{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-sensei{\r} uncovered a wallet from the back of a bookshelf.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:46.39,0:01:49.90,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,And inside, was a message from Ran as a first grader.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:52.44,0:01:54.19,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Ten years ago...
Dialogue: 0,0:01:55.07,0:01:56.61,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,After going into the school at night.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:57.15,0:02:00.57,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Shinichi met his "younger brother, who gave him a riddle...
Dialogue: 0,0:02:01.12,0:02:02.95,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Saying that a treasure awaited him at the end.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:06.83,0:02:08.79,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,"Erase his mark, and..."
Dialogue: 0,0:02:10.04,0:02:12.96,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,With a raspy voice, endure loneliness.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:15.09,0:02:20.30,Dialogue Top,,0,0,0,,Young Kudo Shinichi's Adventure\N(Part Two)
Dialogue: 0,0:02:15.09,0:02:18.26,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Young Kudo Shinichi's Adventure, Part Two!
Dialogue: 0,0:02:24.35,0:02:27.98,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Even if it's talking about the Okuho District,
Dialogue: 0,0:02:27.98,0:02:30.52,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,we don't know what the rest means.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:30.52,0:02:32.23,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Maybe it's about a dentist?
Dialogue: 0,0:02:32.73,0:02:37.90,Signs,,0,0,0,,Note: "Kamishimeru" can mean endure in some cases and the action of "biting" in others.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:32.73,0:02:33.98,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,It does say "bite".
Dialogue: 0,0:02:34.27,0:02:36.57,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,No, there aren't any around.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:37.07,0:02:38.32,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Then, where's it pointing to?
Dialogue: 0,0:02:38.57,0:02:40.32,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Hurry up and tell us, Conan{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-kun{\r}!
Dialogue: 0,0:02:40.66,0:02:45.28,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Now, now, start with he "Erase Okuho's mark part.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:45.41,0:02:46.62,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,I got it!
Dialogue: 0,0:02:46.62,0:02:48.37,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Maybe it's the supermarket?
Dialogue: 0,0:02:48.96,0:02:49.91,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,The supermarket?
Dialogue: 0,0:02:49.91,0:02:51.62,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Why would you think that?
Dialogue: 0,0:02:52.46,0:02:53.33,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,W-Why?
Dialogue: 0,0:02:53.63,0:02:59.01,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Dad always says, "With some management, Mom could erase our deficit."
Dialogue: 0,0:02:59.63,0:03:02.76,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,That's why Mom always gets worried when she goes shopping.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:02.76,0:03:04.05,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,That's not it.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:04.64,0:03:06.81,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,It's not "akaji, it's "akashi'.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:07.39,0:03:11.94,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,It's some kind of mark that can prove a person innocent.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:12.19,0:03:16.11,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Finding the "mark" could refer to scratch-offs...
Dialogue: 0,0:03:16.44,0:03:19.23,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Then, erasing it would be...
Dialogue: 0,0:03:19.44,0:03:20.28,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,A postmark?
Dialogue: 0,0:03:20.70,0:03:22.07,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Then, the place it mentioned...
Dialogue: 0,0:03:22.49,0:03:24.49,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Yeah, that's what Ran{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-neechan{\r} said next.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:26.24,0:03:28.62,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Ten years ago, that guy named Shinichi noticed that, too.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:30.37,0:03:32.58,Dialogue Top,,0,0,0,,10 Years Ago
Dialogue: 0,0:03:32.67,0:03:33.46,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,We need to go to Okuho post office?
Dialogue: 0,0:03:34.21,0:03:36.29,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Oh, does that mean you've solved it, Shinichi?
Dialogue: 0,0:03:36.50,0:03:38.50,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Yeah, half of it.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:38.96,0:03:41.97,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,This "akashi" it's talking about should be a mark, right?
Dialogue: 0,0:03:41.97,0:03:43.68,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,So, erasing the mark would be...
Dialogue: 0,0:03:44.76,0:03:45.55,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,A postmark!
Dialogue: 0,0:03:46.14,0:03:49.14,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,The mark that tells when a stamp was issued.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:49.14,0:03:50.27,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,That's why it's the post office.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:51.06,0:03:52.10,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,But, but...
Dialogue: 0,0:03:52.10,0:03:54.98,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,The post office workers don't hove raspy voices, do they?
Dialogue: 0,0:03:54.98,0:03:55.81,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Right.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:56.06,0:03:58.23,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,I'm not sure about that part,
Dialogue: 0,0:03:59.23,0:04:01.32,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,but if it is the post office, we have to go.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:02.28,0:04:03.03,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Why?
Dialogue: 0,0:04:03.40,0:04:11.45,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Because these codes are about going somewhere, finding another code on something red, and doing it again, right?
Dialogue: 0,0:04:12.00,0:04:13.54,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,The first red thing was a fire hydrant.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:13.96,0:04:15.58,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Then e railroad crossing's warning lights.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:15.58,0:04:18.88,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,And if the third code is about the post office, it's gotta be...
Dialogue: 0,0:04:19.67,0:04:22.21,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,I really love red things.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:23.22,0:04:24.01,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,I got it!
Dialogue: 0,0:04:24.01,0:04:25.01,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,A mailbox!
Dialogue: 0,0:04:25.01,0:04:26.64,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,There should be a red mailbox, right?
Dialogue: 0,0:04:26.89,0:04:27.64,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Exactly.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:33.27,0:04:35.14,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,He took Ran with him!?
Dialogue: 0,0:04:35.14,0:04:36.10,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Shinichi{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-kun{\r} did?
Dialogue: 0,0:04:36.48,0:04:39.52,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Yeah, they went somewhere with Agasa{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-san{\r}.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:40.15,0:04:43.15,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,I think it was... Haido Port.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:43.53,0:04:44.95,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,H-Haido Port?
Dialogue: 0,0:04:45.49,0:04:47.82,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,There was a murder there!
Dialogue: 0,0:04:48.12,0:04:49.70,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Oh, that won't be a problem.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:50.29,0:04:52.95,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,I heard that murder was solved this morning.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:55.92,0:04:57.42,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,It's a holiday, too.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:57.42,0:05:00.09,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,It's better than staying inside and watching TV or playing games.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:00.46,0:05:04.67,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,I think they should be able to go beyond the doors on a grand adventure.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:06.88,0:05:11.43,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Lately, my son has been staying inside reading books all day.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:11.43,0:05:14.43,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,I should be thanking your daughter for taking him outside.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:14.56,0:05:17.64,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,But wasn't it Shinichi{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-kun{\r} who took her?
Dialogue: 0,0:05:17.65,0:05:19.23,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Now, now, don't worry!
Dialogue: 0,0:05:19.77,0:05:21.06,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Jeez...
Dialogue: 0,0:05:21.07,0:05:23.90,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,You're always so carefree, Yuki{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-chan{\r}.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:24.53,0:05:25.49,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Oh, right!
Dialogue: 0,0:05:25.49,0:05:28.82,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,I got a call from the Police HQ for you, Yuusaku{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-san{\r}.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:29.32,0:05:34.33,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,They said, "Thank you for your assistance in helping protect be jewels."
Dialogue: 0,0:05:34.54,0:05:36.00,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Oh, that.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:36.66,0:05:40.08,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,That must be from when you beat that eccentric thief, right?
Dialogue: 0,0:05:40.46,0:05:41.50,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,No, actually...
Dialogue: 0,0:05:42.84,0:05:46.01,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,I should say his escape was he clever part.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:48.47,0:05:51.35,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,But, why'd hey call your house?
Dialogue: 0,0:05:51.35,0:05:53.93,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,They tried to call you all, but the line was out.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:55.10,0:05:56.77,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Oh, I get it, Yuu{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-chan{\r}.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:56.77,0:05:58.27,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,You unplugged the phone again, didn't you?
Dialogue: 0,0:05:58.27,0:06:01.94,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Oh, well, I have to be able to concentrate when my deadlines come up.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:03.02,0:06:06.99,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Well, if those kids coll, tell my daughter to come home immediately.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:08.15,0:06:10.24,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Oh? You're leaving already?
Dialogue: 0,0:06:10.24,0:06:12.57,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,I don't have time to relax right now.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:12.58,0:06:16.33,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,My first trial is coming up next week, so I have to finish preparing for it.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:16.50,0:06:17.66,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,I see.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:17.66,0:06:19.71,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,You'll become a great lawyer, I know it.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:19.83,0:06:20.71,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Good luck!
Dialogue: 0,0:06:20.88,0:06:24.84,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Thanks, but I'll probably lose since it's my first case.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:25.25,0:06:27.46,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,I'll let you cheer me up afterwards, all right?
Dialogue: 0,0:06:27.47,0:06:27.96,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,All right!
Dialogue: 0,0:06:31.47,0:06:35.18,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Oh, that's right, aren't you supposed to meet with someone?
Dialogue: 0,0:06:36.68,0:06:41.31,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,You know, that magician that's training you.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:42.98,0:06:44.11,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,I completely forgot!
Dialogue: 0,0:06:44.11,0:06:46.02,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,I made plans to hand over my latest essay.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:46.82,0:06:47.90,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,I'm gonna be late!
Dialogue: 0,0:06:47.84,0:06:51.11,Dialogue Top,,0,0,0,,Okuho Post Office
Dialogue: 0,0:06:48.74,0:06:51.15,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Hey Shinichi, here's the mailbox...
Dialogue: 0,0:06:51.28,0:06:53.32,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,But there's nothing on it.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:53.37,0:06:56.16,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,How weird, I was sure it was here.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:57.58,0:07:02.96,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,I guess we need to figure out the "with a raspy voice, endure loneliness" part first then, huh?
Dialogue: 0,0:07:05.00,0:07:06.67,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Hello, evening paper!
Dialogue: 0,0:07:07.46,0:07:08.71,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,How's business?
Dialogue: 0,0:07:08.71,0:07:10.67,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,As you can see, the cuckoo is singing.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:11.05,0:07:11.88,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,A singing "kakko"?
Dialogue: 0,0:07:14.01,0:07:14.89,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,What's "kakko"?
Dialogue: 0,0:07:15.14,0:07:15.89,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,It's cuckoo.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:17.10,0:07:18.85,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,It's referring to the "school"!
Dialogue: 0,0:07:18.93,0:07:19.52,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Lets go, Mouri!
Dialogue: 0,0:07:20.73,0:07:21.60,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Mouri?
Dialogue: 0,0:07:27.48,0:07:28.78,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Hey, Shinichi!
Dialogue: 0,0:07:29.07,0:07:30.40,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,I said "Shinichi"!
Dialogue: 0,0:07:30.57,0:07:33.20,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Jeez, didn't I tell you?
Dialogue: 0,0:07:33.20,0:07:34.91,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Don't call me by my first name at school!
Dialogue: 0,0:07:35.24,0:07:36.20,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,It's embarrassing.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:36.95,0:07:38.66,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,But Shinichi is Shinichi, right?
Dialogue: 0,0:07:39.08,0:07:40.95,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Call me "Kudo{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-kun{\r}".
Dialogue: 0,0:07:40.96,0:07:43.79,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,And in turn, I'll call you "Mouri{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-san{\r}".
Dialogue: 0,0:07:45.21,0:07:48.50,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Well, we don't be kids forever.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:48.50,0:07:50.96,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,I'll see you later, Mouri{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-san{\r}.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:54.55,0:07:56.85,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,This is the only red thing near the school.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:59.10,0:08:02.18,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,I can't find anything up here.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:02.19,0:08:04.60,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Look closer! It has to be there!
Dialogue: 0,0:08:05.15,0:08:06.69,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,It's just not up here.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:09.53,0:08:10.94,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,There's something on the pole!
Dialogue: 0,0:08:12.36,0:08:15.45,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Right, since this code was made for kids,
Dialogue: 0,0:08:15.99,0:08:17.57,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,it'd have to be somewhere we can reach.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:19.08,0:08:20.54,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,What's his?
Dialogue: 0,0:08:25.37,0:08:27.13,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,You can't read it either, Professor?
Dialogue: 0,0:08:27.13,0:08:33.34,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,If you try to make something of it, it tries to say "Beika", which is probably the district, but...
Dialogue: 0,0:08:33.80,0:08:35.18,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Maybe it's in Chinese?
Dialogue: 0,0:08:35.34,0:08:38.14,Signs,,0,0,0,,Note: Chuugoku = China
Dialogue: 0,0:08:35.34,0:08:38.14,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,The bit after Beika is read "Chuugoku", right?
Dialogue: 0,0:08:38.64,0:08:42.31,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,That's true, but that doesn't make it Chinese.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:42.89,0:08:44.23,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Beika Middle...
Dialogue: 0,0:08:44.23,0:08:45.73,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Beika Middle School...
Dialogue: 0,0:08:46.69,0:08:47.81,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Is there one?
Dialogue: 0,0:08:47.81,0:08:51.86,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,No, Beika just has a college and a high school.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:52.36,0:08:56.32,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,But why is the last character the only one with a square around it?
Dialogue: 0,0:08:57.32,0:08:58.37,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Well...
Dialogue: 0,0:09:00.79,0:09:01.95,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,I've seen this somewhere before...
Dialogue: 0,0:09:08.96,0:09:09.63,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Dad!
Dialogue: 0,0:09:10.75,0:09:12.63,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,What're you all doing here out here?
Dialogue: 0,0:09:13.67,0:09:16.63,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Ah, actually I...
Dialogue: 0,0:09:16.72,0:09:21.47,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,T-The Professor mode us a code and we're trying to solve it.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:22.10,0:09:22.76,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Right, Professor?
Dialogue: 0,0:09:23.64,0:09:24.89,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Yeah, pretty much.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:26.19,0:09:26.81,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,A code?
Dialogue: 0,0:09:27.14,0:09:28.81,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Dad, why're you here?
Dialogue: 0,0:09:29.15,0:09:35.53,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Oh, see, the killer we caught this morning used to work at that post office,
Dialogue: 0,0:09:35.53,0:09:37.36,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,so the Lieutenant Inspector and I came for statements.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:37.45,0:09:41.32,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,You know, seeing hem solving codes brings back memories.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:41.33,0:09:44.95,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,When I was a child, my friends and I used to make codes and pretend to be spies.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:45.96,0:09:48.37,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,But this one's too hard to get.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:48.67,0:09:50.21,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Well, let me see it.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:50.75,0:09:52.88,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,All right, bu it's really hard.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:53.38,0:09:56.67,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,What're you trying to say!? We're police officers!
Dialogue: 0,0:09:56.67,0:10:00.51,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,A little, simple riddle made for children is nothing to us.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:09.31,0:10:11.48,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Hey, Mouri{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-kun{\r}, do you get it?
Dialogue: 0,0:10:12.11,0:10:13.98,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,No, not at all...
Dialogue: 0,0:10:14.44,0:10:16.65,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Well, now! It's a clever code.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:16.65,0:10:18.99,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,But it may be too hard for kids.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:19.70,0:10:21.82,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,What? Couldn't get it either?
Dialogue: 0,0:10:21.95,0:10:26.20,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Hey, Lieutenant Inspector, how about some Mahjong tonight?
Dialogue: 0,0:10:26.20,0:10:29.04,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Oh! 1 was thinking the exact same thing!
Dialogue: 0,0:10:29.29,0:10:34.25,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,I dunno why, but seeing that code mode me wanna play Mahjong.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:34.80,0:10:36.50,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,What? You, too?
Dialogue: 0,0:10:37.84,0:10:38.55,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Mahjong?
Dialogue: 0,0:10:39.22,0:10:42.05,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Bye Ran, be sure to get home soon!
Dialogue: 0,0:10:42.51,0:10:43.05,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Yes!
Dialogue: 0,0:10:50.90,0:10:55.52,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Shinichi, this is a game from China called "Mahjong".
Dialogue: 0,0:10:56.07,0:11:02.03,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Just like in Seven Bridge, in order to win, you hove to draw the last waiting tile or use another player's.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:02.74,0:11:04.91,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,But, what makes it different from Seven Bridge is...
Dialogue: 0,0:11:04.91,0:11:07.62,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,In Mahjong, like Poker, you earn have a complete hand.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:08.04,0:11:10.12,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,This, which is either "tonba" or "nanba",
Dialogue: 0,0:11:10.87,0:11:13.75,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,is the rule that allows "ba" to control the game.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:15.67,0:11:16.25,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Mahjong?
Dialogue: 0,0:11:17.09,0:11:20.17,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,You think this code has something to do with Mahjong?
Dialogue: 0,0:11:21.38,0:11:23.72,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,I think we can solve it with Mahjong.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:25.14,0:11:30.60,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,I know the third character, "chuu" and the last one "higashi" are on Mahjong tiles.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:31.52,0:11:33.94,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,The others aren't on Mahjong tiles.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:34.06,0:11:39.48,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,For the first two, we can just assume they refer to the Beika District.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:40.11,0:11:44.11,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,The last character, "higashi", surrounded by a square is "ba" in Mahjong.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:44.62,0:11:47.33,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,See, that means it's either "tanba" or "nanba", right?
Dialogue: 0,0:11:47.83,0:11:50.08,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,The two characters on top are read "kokushi".
Dialogue: 0,0:11:50.37,0:11:54.83,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,It's one of the complete hands, called "kokushimusou", which is when you can get 1, 9, and the other character tiles.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:55.08,0:11:57.34,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,But what about the "chuu" on top of that?
Dialogue: 0,0:11:58.09,0:12:01.01,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Well, I guess the Mahjong tile "dora" may do it.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:01.01,0:12:04.22,Signs,,0,0,0,,Note: machi = waiting
Dialogue: 0,0:12:01.01,0:12:04.22,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Oh, wait, since it's a kokushi, it'd probably be a "machi" tile.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:06.60,0:12:09.22,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,And? When you read all three together?
Dialogue: 0,0:12:09.81,0:12:12.93,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Machi... yaku... ba?
Dialogue: 0,0:12:13.81,0:12:15.60,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,I see! It's City Hall!
Dialogue: 0,0:12:17.44,0:12:24.32,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,I see, and without a city hall in Beika, it must mean the branch office.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:24.61,0:12:25.91,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Yep, let's go!
Dialogue: 0,0:12:30.62,0:12:31.70,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,It isn't here.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:31.87,0:12:33.29,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,It's not here, Shinichi.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:33.29,0:12:35.21,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,There's nothing red here.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:35.92,0:12:38.25,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Oh, it's already late in the evening...
Dialogue: 0,0:12:38.67,0:12:42.88,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Shinichi, why don't we go home and continue tomorrow?
Dialogue: 0,0:12:42.88,0:12:45.80,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Since you're out of school for Golden Week, it'll be fine.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:45.80,0:12:46.84,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Golden Week?
Dialogue: 0,0:12:47.22,0:12:49.35,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,I see, it's a holiday!
Dialogue: 0,0:12:50.51,0:12:52.72,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,It is, but what's that mean?
Dialogue: 0,0:12:53.27,0:12:55.73,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Since it's the ward office, it should be up...
Dialogue: 0,0:13:03.44,0:13:04.15,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,"The End"?
Dialogue: 0,0:13:09.03,0:13:10.53,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Is this English?
Dialogue: 0,0:13:10.62,0:13:14.29,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Well, those are just "W" and "S" from the alphabet.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:14.37,0:13:16.75,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,I don't know what the arrow means, though.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:18.00,0:13:21.46,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,But since it says "the end", this should be the last one.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:22.51,0:13:25.63,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Do "W and "S" mean anything by themselves?
Dialogue: 0,0:13:27.84,0:13:30.72,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,That's right! They're directions!
Dialogue: 0,0:13:30.72,0:13:35.98,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,"S" stands for South, while "W" stands for West!
Dialogue: 0,0:13:36.35,0:13:39.81,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,So it's telling us o go from South to West?
Dialogue: 0,0:13:41.90,0:13:46.32,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Maybe the arrow is meant to tell us to look in those directions?
Dialogue: 0,0:13:46.70,0:13:49.20,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,South is that way...
Dialogue: 0,0:13:49.32,0:13:49.82,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,West is...
Dialogue: 0,0:13:50.53,0:13:51.37,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,This way.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:58.37,0:13:59.21,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,It's beautiful!
Dialogue: 0,0:14:02.00,0:14:03.17,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,I see.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:03.17,0:14:04.30,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,So that's it.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:05.21,0:14:06.42,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,I know now.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:06.42,0:14:08.09,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,I know who made the code.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:08.93,0:14:09.80,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Who is it?
Dialogue: 0,0:14:10.64,0:14:11.80,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,My Dad.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:12.35,0:14:17.56,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,He asked a friend to give us the code to get us here...
Dialogue: 0,0:14:18.89,0:14:20.77,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,To view the sunset.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:21.61,0:14:27.32,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,It was probably because I've been inside reading a lot lately.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:27.61,0:14:34.41,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,But the only reason you went to the school last night was because of a ghost story you heard by chance, right?
Dialogue: 0,0:14:34.91,0:14:39.58,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Sonoko{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-chan{\r} said she heard it from a man who delivered books to the library.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:39.58,0:14:41.46,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,He told her about the ghost.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:42.04,0:14:45.46,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,That was probably the guy who was there last night.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:45.59,0:14:46.71,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,I see.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:46.71,0:14:55.05,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,All he had to do was mention it to Ran{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-kun{\r}'s friend, which would mean it would get back to you, who loves mysteries.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:55.47,0:14:56.68,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Exactly.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:57.02,0:15:00.73,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,To put it simply, we were manipulated by my Dad this entire time.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:02.06,0:15:03.61,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,But aren't you glad?
Dialogue: 0,0:15:03.61,0:15:05.82,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,We got to see such a pretty sunset.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:06.36,0:15:10.03,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Yeah, I'd rather not admit it, but I feel the same, Ran.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:11.66,0:15:13.82,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Oh, I mean... Mouri.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:13.82,0:15:15.70,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,I like Ran!
Dialogue: 0,0:15:15.70,0:15:16.95,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,I wanna hear Ran!
Dialogue: 0,0:15:20.54,0:15:22.08,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Is that...
Dialogue: 0,0:15:27.05,0:15:28.80,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,If you want...
Dialogue: 0,0:15:29.76,0:15:30.97,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,I guess it's OK.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:31.34,0:15:32.55,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Really!?
Dialogue: 0,0:15:32.55,0:15:34.26,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,That's great, Shinichi!
Dialogue: 0,0:15:36.22,0:15:37.81,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Lemme go!
Dialogue: 0,0:15:39.35,0:15:42.35,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,I need to thank your dad!
Dialogue: 0,0:15:42.35,0:15:48.27,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Stupid, if anyone, thank my Dad's friend who gave us the code and is watching us now.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:50.28,0:15:52.45,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,That guy's around here watching?
Dialogue: 0,0:15:52.86,0:15:53.70,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Yeah.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:53.70,0:15:58.16,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,To be able to show us the sunset, he'd have to keep an eye on us the whole time, right?
Dialogue: 0,0:15:59.16,0:16:02.71,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Otherwise, he wouldn't know how long it'd take us to finish each one.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:03.96,0:16:08.17,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,He had to watch us so that-when we had solved one message,
Dialogue: 0,0:16:08.21,0:16:10.63,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,he'd be able to control the timing by switching the next one out.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:10.97,0:16:15.68,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,guess that's how he was able to time when we got here.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:16.26,0:16:19.60,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,But couldn't that have been your dad?
Dialogue: 0,0:16:20.10,0:16:23.10,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,No, he would have stepped out and said:
Dialogue: 0,0:16:23.10,0:16:25.40,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,"Took you long enough."
Dialogue: 0,0:16:26.19,0:16:28.15,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Hey, guy from lost night!
Dialogue: 0,0:16:28.77,0:16:30.32,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,You're listening, right?
Dialogue: 0,0:16:30.94,0:16:33.70,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,We're going to put a message for you in the wallet!
Dialogue: 0,0:16:33.70,0:16:34.65,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Come get it later!
Dialogue: 0,0:16:35.95,0:16:40.12,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,We'll put it behind that gentleman thief book you were reading!
Dialogue: 0,0:16:40.12,0:16:41.87,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Please come get it!
Dialogue: 0,0:16:46.13,0:16:54.09,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,So, that's why there's a piece of paper with "Thank you, Class 1-A Mouri Ran" written on it in this wallet.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:55.43,0:16:56.93,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,That was such a wonderful story!
Dialogue: 0,0:16:56.93,0:17:00.35,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,But the book in front of the wallet...
Dialogue: 0,0:17:00.76,0:17:03.02,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Wasn't one about a gentleman thief.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:03.39,0:17:04.89,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,That's probably because...
Dialogue: 0,0:17:05.27,0:17:09.52,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,The arrangement of the books has changed over the last ten years.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:09.94,0:17:14.44,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,But still, whoever that was never came to pick up the message.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:14.45,0:17:18.53,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Even if the arrangement changed, he'd know where it was.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:19.83,0:17:20.78,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,That's true.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:21.24,0:17:23.45,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,But the one who came up with the codes...
Dialogue: 0,0:17:23.45,0:17:26.00,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,I think he ran out of ideas near the end.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:26.00,0:17:26.62,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Why?
Dialogue: 0,0:17:27.12,0:17:30.59,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Because, at the beginning, the riddles were very interesting,
Dialogue: 0,0:17:30.59,0:17:34.63,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,but the last one was just "S" and "W", saying "look west".
Dialogue: 0,0:17:35.01,0:17:36.26,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,That's what I mean.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:40.97,0:17:42.06,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,My reasoning back then was wrong!
Dialogue: 0,0:17:42.81,0:17:46.68,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,If he wanted to show us the sun, the "W" would've sufficed.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:46.69,0:17:48.48,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,The arrow and "S" wouldn't have been needed!
Dialogue: 0,0:17:49.73,0:17:51.36,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Then, what were they for...
Dialogue: 0,0:17:51.36,0:17:53.23,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,The "S, "W" and the arrow?
Dialogue: 0,0:17:54.40,0:17:57.70,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Why was the last one just a direction?
Dialogue: 0,0:18:03.08,0:18:05.83,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,The first was a port...
Dialogue: 0,0:18:08.87,0:18:10.46,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,The second was the shape of a castle...
Dialogue: 0,0:18:12.38,0:18:15.09,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,The third was floodgates...
Dialogue: 0,0:18:17.63,0:18:18.76,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,A middle school...
Dialogue: 0,0:18:26.68,0:18:28.35,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,He looks sunk in thought.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:29.81,0:18:34.82,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Actually, the post office code started with erasing a "mark', with "mark being encircled...
Dialogue: 0,0:18:34.82,0:18:38.15,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,So, if you "erased" the circle...
Dialogue: 0,0:18:39.74,0:18:46.37,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Then, if you wrote down the symbols vertically as I asked before...
Dialogue: 0,0:18:47.70,0:18:50.87,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,And if "S" to "W" meant to turn it 90 degrees...
Dialogue: 0,0:18:51.46,0:18:53.58,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,That means it would be...
Dialogue: 0,0:18:59.17,0:19:00.72,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Oxhide...
Dialogue: 0,0:19:01.47,0:19:02.34,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Leather!?
Dialogue: 0,0:19:03.68,0:19:04.60,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,It's the wallet!
Dialogue: 0,0:19:09.18,0:19:10.31,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,We were wrong!
Dialogue: 0,0:19:10.77,0:19:12.98,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,He wasn't watching then!
Dialogue: 0,0:19:13.73,0:19:18.53,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,We'll put it behind that gentlemen thief book you were reading!
Dialogue: 0,0:19:18.53,0:19:20.11,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Please come get it!
Dialogue: 0,0:19:21.07,0:19:22.11,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Conan{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-kun{\r}?
Dialogue: 0,0:19:22.11,0:19:22.91,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Hey!
Dialogue: 0,0:19:22.91,0:19:23.82,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,What's wrong?
Dialogue: 0,0:19:24.24,0:19:26.12,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,I see, that's it!
Dialogue: 0,0:19:26.79,0:19:28.83,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,This code, there's no way a kid could solve it.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:31.33,0:19:33.58,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,This code was meant for Dad!
Dialogue: 0,0:19:34.08,0:19:37.38,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,He thought that I'd go to Dad after I got stuck.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:38.84,0:19:41.76,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,That means, ten years ago...
Dialogue: 0,0:19:41.76,0:19:43.30,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,The one who gave it to us was...
Dialogue: 0,0:19:44.97,0:19:47.47,Dialogue Top,,0,0,0,,10 Years Ago
Dialogue: 0,0:19:48.35,0:19:52.98,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Well then, thank you very much.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:53.65,0:19:56.36,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,No, it's likely just someone spreading a rumor.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:57.90,0:20:03.24,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,After all, we magic-ions are con artists that play tricks when people aren't looking.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:03.24,0:20:06.49,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Oh, now, a con artist?
Dialogue: 0,0:20:06.70,0:20:10.49,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,It's such a shame that Mr. Kudo couldn't make it.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:10.75,0:20:14.00,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Actually, I should say I'm relieved.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:14.67,0:20:18.38,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,My tricks are nothing but a house built of sand in his eyes.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:18.75,0:20:20.50,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,I feel as if he can see through them all.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:21.34,0:20:22.55,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Don't be modest.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:23.05,0:20:26.55,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,You're one of my "Seven Knights that I've met".
Dialogue: 0,0:20:26.55,0:20:28.10,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,You really are, Kuroba Toichi.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:29.06,0:20:31.81,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Those essays, I love reading them.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:31.81,0:20:32.98,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,I'm quite a fan.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:35.31,0:20:36.44,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,You can have this!
Dialogue: 0,0:20:36.44,0:20:37.65,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,You're such a pretty old lady!
Dialogue: 0,0:20:40.44,0:20:42.86,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Hey, Kaitou, don't be so bothersome.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:43.28,0:20:45.36,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,What an energetic child you have!
Dialogue: 0,0:20:46.07,0:20:47.20,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,But, did you know...
Dialogue: 0,0:20:48.12,0:20:51.87,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,You aren't supposed to use "pretty" and "old lady" together!?
Dialogue: 0,0:20:55.12,0:20:56.75,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Since Mr. Kudo couldn't make it...
Dialogue: 0,0:20:57.08,0:21:03.21,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,A letter from my friend will arrive for him later, so if you could have him reply to this address...
Dialogue: 0,0:21:03.22,0:21:05.72,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Oh, that's for the fan letter to Yuusaku, right?
Dialogue: 0,0:21:06.51,0:21:11.39,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,When I told him about it, he wrote you a reply and had me bring it.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:11.72,0:21:15.35,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,But, I wouldn't really call it a "reply"...
Dialogue: 0,0:21:15.60,0:21:16.23,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Wait!
Dialogue: 0,0:21:17.06,0:21:21.11,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,It's just a simple exclamation mark.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:21.11,0:21:22.11,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Am I right?
Dialogue: 0,0:21:23.65,0:21:24.15,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Yeah...
Dialogue: 0,0:21:25.28,0:21:27.24,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,But, how'd you...
Dialogue: 0,0:21:28.62,0:21:30.62,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,As should be expected from the one who named me.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:31.87,0:21:35.00,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,My friend's letter was the same.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:36.25,0:21:38.83,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,It was just one symbol.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:41.96,0:21:44.09,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Dear Yuusaku Kudo...
Dialogue: 0,0:21:44.97,0:21:46.80,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Kaitou No. 1412.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:48.18,0:21:49.47,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,That's right, she said...
Dialogue: 0,0:21:49.93,0:21:52.51,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Yuusoku is the parent of the name Kid!
Dialogue: 0,0:21:52.97,0:21:58.77,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,A reporter jotted down "1412", which Yuusoku read as "K.I.D."
Dialogue: 0,0:22:00.15,0:22:02.77,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,I'm your sibling.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:02.77,0:22:05.40,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Well, maybe I should say, your younger brother.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:05.74,0:22:07.49,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,So that's what he meant then.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:08.03,0:22:10.07,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Are you gonna be able to stop me next time?
Dialogue: 0,0:22:11.12,0:22:12.07,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Yeah...
Dialogue: 0,0:22:12.08,0:22:13.03,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Of course!
Dialogue: 0,0:22:13.91,0:22:16.16,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,But, what's this supposed to mean?
Dialogue: 0,0:22:16.16,0:22:17.41,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,This question mark...
